From: Song Liu <song@kernel.org>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2025 22:00:01 -0700
Subject: bpf/veristat: Fix veristat for map type BPF_MAP_TYPE_CGRP_STORAGE
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
Git-commit: ccefa19335a0b81f11b0856e951ca909445b3783
References: jsc#PED-14653

BPF_MAP_TYPE_CGRP_STORAGE doesn't allow non-zero max_entries. So veristat
should not set it to 1.

Signed-off-by: Song Liu <song@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Andrii Nakryiko <andrii@kernel.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/bpf/20250613050001.1058733-1-song@kernel.org
Acked-by: Hoyeon Lee <hoyeon.lee@suse.com>
---
 tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c
+++ b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c
@@ -1182,6 +1182,7 @@ static void fixup_obj(struct bpf_object
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_TASK_STORAGE:
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_INODE_STORAGE:
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_CGROUP_STORAGE:
+		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_CGRP_STORAGE:
 			break;
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_STRUCT_OPS:
 			mask_unrelated_struct_ops_progs(obj, map, prog);
